The paper deals with the problem of counting the number of answers to a first-order formula on a finite structure, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper presents an extension of first-order logic that allows for expressing algorithms for this counting problem. This topic is closely related to several areas of computer science, including logic (cs.LO), data structures (cs.DS), databases (cs.DB), computational complexity (cs.CC), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
